# Livotale Design Standards

## Brand colors (never hardcode alternatives)

- Primary pink: `#D7316C` — use `text-livotale-pink`, `bg-livotale-pink`
- Primary teal: `#1EABB3` — use `text-livotale-teal`, `bg-livotale-teal`
- Gradients: `from-livotale-pink to-livotale-teal` for CTAs and hero accents

## Typography

- Font: Inter (loaded in index.html); fallback system-ui
- Landing hero H1: `text-4xl sm:text-5xl lg:text-6xl xl:text-7xl font-extrabold`
- Section H2: `text-3xl md:text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-bold`
- Body: `text-base md:text-lg leading-relaxed`
- Labels/badges: `text-xs sm:text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest`

## Landing (dark theme)

- Background: `bg-black` / `bg-neutral-950`
- Text: `text-white` headings, `text-neutral-300/400` body
- Cards: `border border-white/10 bg-white/[0.02]`
- Full-bleed sections: use `left-1/2 -ml-[50vw] w-screen` pattern sparingly

## Admin (light theme)

- Background: `bg-background` / `bg-card`
- Use shadcn/ui components; do not invent one-off button styles
- Sidebar: collapsed 72px, expanded 256px — match AdminLayout

## Spacing

- Section padding: `py-16 md:py-24`
- Container: `max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6`
- Card padding: `p-6 md:p-8`

## Components

- Primary CTA: gradient button or WhatsAppButton for booking
- Secondary: outline with brand border (`border-livotale-teal/40`)
- Icons: lucide-react in admin; consistent `h-5 w-5` or `h-6 w-6`

## Accessibility

- All images need meaningful `alt`
- Interactive elements need `aria-label` when icon-only
- Maintain 4.5:1 contrast on body text
